&lt;h4 id=&quot;weapon-swap&quot;&gt;Weapon Swap&lt;&#x2F;h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Weapon swap is optional&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dagger&#x2F;Dagger&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dagger&#x2F;Torch&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Axe&#x2F;Dagger&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dagger&#x2F;Axe&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ol&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;td&gt;&lt;&#x2F;tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td colspan=2 style=&quot;white-space: normal;&quot;&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;small&gt;&lt;em&gt;Dagger&#x2F;Axe (Axe 4 can proc &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;traits&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;2127&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Twice as Vicious) runs on a similar concept and will do similar damage on a hybrid build. However, a ranged build is simpler to play.&lt;&#x2F;em&gt;&lt;&#x2F;small&gt;&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;blockquote&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;td&gt;&lt;&#x2F;tr&gt;&lt;&#x2F;table&gt;
&lt;hr &#x2F;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Optimised Viper&#x27;s Loadout
&lt;a rel=&quot;noopener&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;https:&#x2F;&#x2F;gw2skills.net&#x2F;editor&#x2F;?POQAUlZUw+YSMKmJWaXXP3ca3+4hDB-DSRYfBFaGFcehRaBEmAG&#x2F;KoJFnVgKA-e&quot;&gt;GW2Skills Link&lt;&#x2F;a&gt;&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&quot;relic&quot;&gt;Relic&lt;&#x2F;h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;items&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;104424&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Relic of Thorns (default)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;items&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;100153&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Relic of the Fractal (test)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;small&gt;It is not possible to bench &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;items&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;104424&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Relic of Thorns due to the conditions required to trigger it at the golem.&lt;&#x2F;small&gt;&lt;br&#x2F;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;small&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;items&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;102199&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Relic of the Blightbringer has been considered but remains a much weaker version as there is a hidden ICD, preventing
Poison Volley from proccing multiple times.&lt;&#x2F;small&gt;&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ul&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&quot;food&quot;&gt;Food&lt;&#x2F;h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;items&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;91878&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Cilantro and Cured Meat Flatbread&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;items&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;43361&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Koi Cake(budget alternative)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ul&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&quot;utility&quot;&gt;Utility&lt;&#x2F;h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;items&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;48917&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Toxic Tuning Crystal&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ul&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&quot;pets&quot;&gt;Pets&lt;&#x2F;h4&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The Janthiri Bee is competitive in damage and provides ready access CC, making it the default best option for raiding.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The Wallow provides a poison field, decent healing and condition cleanses which is good in open world.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Other options include the Bristleback, Jungle Spider, Jaguar, Warthog and Black Widow.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ol&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;blockquote&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;build&quot;&gt;Build&lt;&#x2F;h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Condi DPS\&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;pre data-lang=&quot;chatlink&quot; class=&quot;language-chatlink z-code&quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-chatlink&quot; data-lang=&quot;chatlink&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-source z-chatlink&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-punctuation z-definition z-string z-begin&quot;&gt;[&amp;amp;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;DQQeLSAXNy55AHgAvwAAAOkWAAAbAAAALhYAAEdAEz8AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA=&lt;span class=&quot;z-punctuation z-definition z-string z-end&quot;&gt;]&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;&#x2F;code&gt;&lt;&#x2F;pre&gt;
&lt;hr &#x2F;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;peticon&quot; style=&quot;background: url(&#x27;https:&#x2F;&#x2F;render.guildwars2.com&#x2F;file&#x2F;58AFDFDFDDB8325F5E076C2400C63D450C15EA09&#x2F;2604592.png&#x27;) 50% 50% no-repeat;&quot;&gt;Juvenile Wallow&lt;&#x2F;div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;peticon&quot; style=&quot;background: url(&#x27;https:&#x2F;&#x2F;render.guildwars2.com&#x2F;file&#x2F;03BF0B1C079C06B359E0CE520E747AC5E878F395&#x2F;3594054.png&#x27;) 50% 50% no-repeat;&quot;&gt;Juvenile Janthiri Bee&lt;&#x2F;div&gt;&lt;div data-armory-embed=&#x27;skills&#x27; data-armory-ids=&#x27;31914,12537,40498,12476,45717&#x27;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;div&gt;&lt;div data-armory-embed=&#x27;specializations&#x27; data-armory-ids=&#x27;30,32,55&#x27; data-armory-30-traits=&#x27;1069,1846,1912&#x27; data-armory-32-traits=&#x27;1606,975,1945&#x27; data-armory-55-traits=&#x27;2071,2161,2128&#x27;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;div&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&quot;trait-alternatives&quot;&gt;Trait Alternatives&lt;&#x2F;h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The equipment stats are fairly similar to the that of &lt;a rel=&quot;noopener&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;https:&#x2F;&#x2F;snowcrows.com&#x2F;builds&#x2F;raids&#x2F;ranger&#x2F;condition-soulbeast&quot;&gt;SnowCrows&lt;&#x2F;a&gt; with selection of different traits.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;rotation-and-utilities&quot;&gt;Rotation and Utilities&lt;&#x2F;h2&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&quot;dps-rotation&quot;&gt;DPS Rotation&lt;&#x2F;h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stay merged at all times.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Early Precast - &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;12476&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Spike Trap&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pre-battle - &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;45717&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; One Wolf Pack + &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;12537&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Sharpening Stone + &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;40498&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Vulture Stance + &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;45479&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Sharpen Spines (if using Bristleback)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;General Rotation - Use all non-healing skills on cooldown except F1&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ol&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;blockquote&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&quot;crowd-control&quot;&gt;Crowd Control&lt;&#x2F;h4&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have decent CC by just using &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;12508&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Concussion Shot (Shortbow 4)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have many other CC skills littered in your weapon&#x2F;pet&#x2F;utility kit including the ones used to upkeep &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;traits&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;2127&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Twice as Vicious (see below).&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You can precast &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;12537&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Sharpening Stone for additional CC just before the CC phase of an encounter.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Your Pet F3 skill does a taunt. This is counted as decent CC.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ol&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;blockquote&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&quot;sustainability&quot;&gt;Sustainability&lt;&#x2F;h4&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You may opt to take &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;12489&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Healing Spring for better condi cleanse&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;12517&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Quick Shot (Shortbow 3) is an evade that does a step back. This is useful for bosses with pull mechanics.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;If you need an extra heal, you may swap your pet to the Wallow for &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;44626&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Spiritual Reprieve&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ol&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;blockquote&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;optimisation&quot;&gt;Optimisation&lt;&#x2F;h2&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&quot;twice-as-vicious&quot;&gt;Twice as Vicious&lt;&#x2F;h4&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Spread out &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;12537&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Sharpening Stone, &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;40588&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Primal Cry and &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;12508&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Concussion Shot to maximise &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;traits&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;2127&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Twice as Vicious uptime.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use your other pet CC skills if your coverage is falling such as &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;75771&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Bumble.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You may wish to delay using &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;12508&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Concussion Shot as it is a potent CC skill.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ol&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;blockquote&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&quot;dodging&quot;&gt;Dodging&lt;&#x2F;h4&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Where dodging is necessary, you may delay &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;12517&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Quick Shot by 4s after the dodge to have better uptime of &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;traits&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;1912&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Light on your Feet.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;It is better to use &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;12517&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Quick Shot to dodge once if you don&#x27;t need to dodge twice for better DPS uptime.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ol&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;blockquote&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&quot;raid-ready&quot;&gt;Raid Ready&lt;&#x2F;h4&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;W1 Gorseval - Immobilise with &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;12580&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Entangle during the split phase.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;W2 Slothasor - Jaguar is useful for &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;43375&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Prelude Lash to pull slublings. Make sure to point your bow away from ally slubs!&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;W2 Bandit Trio - The range, self sustainability and high amounts of CC allows this build to do mortars.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;W3 Escort - For backwarg, bring &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;12580&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Entangle and use &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;12507&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Crippling Shot to immobilise. For frontwarg, black widow&#x2F;jungle spider is useful for &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;43375&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Prelude Lash to pull white mantle and &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;44097&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Entangling Web provides meaningul immobilise uptime on the frontwarg.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;W4 Cairn - This build does superb on Cairn, no adjustment is necessary, though you may wish to use &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;31914&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; &quot;We Heal As One!&quot; if you are baiting red circles for the group. Also see dodge section above as you will very often be dodging to move if celestial dash is unavailable.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;W4 Samarog - &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;12476&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Spike Trap can be used to launch Rigom, although the pushback from longbow and using a power build is preferred.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;W5 Dhuum - Use &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;12517&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Quick Shot during the suck phase.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;W6 This build is excellent on Twin Largos as it is.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;This build can be used to pylon kite. Camp shortbow with Juvenile Hawk. Switch to sword. You movement skills are &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;12521&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Swoop (catch) and &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;44991&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Swoop(return). Take note that unlike other kiting classes, your return skill cannot survive dashing through fires.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ol&gt;
